The CANSA Shavathon teams have become a well-known sight in the Lowveld. They popped up at various places over the weekend. The teams could be seen in Riverside Mall on February 24 and at i’langa Mall and White River Crossing the following day.  As an added bonus for the public, some Pumas players also joined in on the spraying fun. ALSO READ: Entrepreneurship seminar in Mbombela looks to the future of Mbombela’s youth Whether you shave it all off or get one green or purple line across your head, next time you see the team somewhere, consider supporting them – it is all for a good cause!         